  "title": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Epilepsy due to immune disorders"
  },
  "definition": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Epilepsy in relation to immunological or autoimmune disorders, such as systemic lupus erythematosus [1], inflammatory bowel disease [2], and antibody associated encephalitis (e.g. NMDA receptors) [3]. Antibody associated encephalitis is often a limbic encephalitis, and is sometimes paraneoplastic. Excludes multiple sclerosis and other demyelinating disorders."
